  {
   "question": "Where does Arms Warrior Phase 5 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 216 top-ranked Arms Warrior DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 5 (Sunwell Plateau), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Arms Warrior items in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Onslaught Bracers (93%), Onslaught Treads (93%), Onslaught Belt (92%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Sunwell Plateau."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should an Arms Warrior use in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Inscribed Pyrestone, Smooth Lionseye and Steady Seaspray Emerald in the coloured sockets. Phase 5 is where the epic gems from Sunwell replace their rare equivalents — that swap alone is worth several item levels across a full set."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does an Arms Warrior need in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Might of the Scourge on shoulders and Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
